title: Accessibility
description: The Metropolitan Washington Airports Authority is fully committed to providing universal access to all public facilities and services at Washington Dulles International Airport for all of its patrons. Washington, DC, is considered one of the most accessible cities in the United States. The Metropolitan Washington Airports Authority is working to ensure that this very important gateway to our Nation's Capital is also accessible to all patrons. For more information visit: http://www.metwashairports.com/dulles/5327.htm

title: Parking
description:
Garage 1
Dulles offers two modern parking garages with a combined 8,325 spaces located close to the terminal. Both garages provide covered parking with easy access to the terminal by either covered pedestrian walkways or shuttle service. The garages are equipped with an automated space counting system, which indicates how many open spaces are available on each level of the garage. $4/hour, $17/day

title: Parking
description:
Terminal/Hourly Parking
Terminal / Hourly parking is located directly across from the terminal and is the closest self-parking parking option at Dulles. Terminal / Hourly parking is great for customers parking to drop off or meet travelers or for customers wishing to park for their own flights. $5/hour, $35/day

title: Parking
description:
Economy Parking
The Economy parking lot, located on airport property near the Dulles Access Road and Route 28 airport exits, offers more than 12,000 parking spaces just minutes by shuttle from the terminal. Shuttle service to and from the terminal is provided 24 hours per day, 7 days per week and scheduled at 10 minute intervals to pick up and drop off at the more than 25 bus shelters located throughout the lot. Customers returning from their trip board the Economy shuttle buses on the ground transportation level of the roadway at the terminal. $5/hour, $10/day

title: Taxis and Public Transportation
description: Silver Line Express, Arrivals Level Door 4. Dulles International Airport Silver Line Express offers first-rate travel at economy prices. You'll ride on comfortable, climate-controlled buses to and from Washington Dulles International Airport at an exceptionally low fare. Best of all, you'll enjoy free Wi-Fi service, ample seating, plenty of luggage storage and front-door service.

title: Taxis and Public Transportation
description: Washington Flyer Taxi provides Washington Dulles International Airport patrons with world-class taxicab service to and from the Airport. Washington Flyer Taxis are competitively priced and fares are calculated by meters. The electronic meter should be activated to compute your fare upon your departure.
